description:
This route is fairly long but rather unchallenging. We leave from Makino and follow a cycleway along the lake shore for the majority of the way. We break from this path only once; to detour through the town of Takashima. This cuts a number of kilometres off our total and also allows us to stock up on supplies. Continuing south we reach the beautiful Shirahige Shrine, where we plan to have lunch. After we continue following the lake the entirety of the way until we reach the very southern tip. 

We then have some small climbs to make in order to reach Kyoto. The first is a push through the steep and narrow Kozeki pass, passing directly over the Lake Biwa Canal tunnel. On the other side we follow the canal through Kyotoâ€™s Yamashina Ward, winding our way past many beautiful Sakura trees. At the end of our path we pour out onto the main road, where we start our final climb of the day - emerging on the other side in Kyoto proper.
